@Stephen59915646 @HuChenAn I think everyone who has been exposed to the Chinese Internet knows what kind of public opinion status Chinese male talent show stars have on the Internet.
“People have no prejudice against talent show stars” is too much of a foreign guest, right?
In addition, letting an idol who is marketed to women turn to endorse the NBA, a male market, is nothing more than the capital hoping to attract more women/fan circles to pay attention to this event through this move. The term “infiltration” of capital is a very accurate one.
